\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Schematic representation of the Threshold Competition Model.} The process unfolds in stages: (1) Authors from population $N$ submit papers into pool $V$; (2) Peer review filters submissions into a set of peer-accepted papers $M$; (3) The volume $M$ is compared against the journal storage capacity $K$. If $M > K$, a rationing mechanism is triggered, reducing the conditional acceptance probability $\rho $ below 1.}}{2}{}\protected@file@percent }
