\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Structure of the Reduced Evolutionary Game.} The author population evolves between two strategies: Only Good (OG) and Always Submit (AS). The Journal acts as a fixed mechanism consisting of a peer review filter and a capacity constraint. Submissions from AS authors increase the total volume $M$, triggering the capacity constraint. The resulting \textbf  {Congestion Externality} ($\bar  {\rho }$) reduces the publication probability for all papers, feeding back into the payoffs and driving the evolutionary dynamics.}}{9}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:reduced_game}{{2}{9}{}{figure.2}{}}
